#calculatingDamage.helpSlide
  h3 calculating damage 
    span(style='font-size:12px;font-weight:normal;color:var(--BACKTOTOP);' onclick="scrollToThisDiv('playGameForward')") [back to top]
  p
    | the amount of damage done in an autoattack is typically calculated by 
    span(style='color: var(--GENERALHIGHLIGHT);') dividing the attacker's ATK by their opponent&apos;s DEF.
  p there are six status effects that modify this base amount of damage, or other hero aspects:
  ol
    li
      span(style='color:var(--STATUSEFFECTCOLOR);') charmed:
      |  DEF is reduced by 50%
    li
      span(style='color:var(--STATUSEFFECTCOLOR);')  distracted:
      |  prevented from gaining MP, DEF reduced by 25%
    li
      span(style='color:var(--STATUSEFFECTCOLOR);')  poisoned:
      |  receives 800/DEF damage each turn
    li
      span(style='color:var(--STATUSEFFECTCOLOR);')  stunned:
      |  ATK and MVT are reduced to zero, RC reduced to 1
    li
      span(style='color:var(--STATUSEFFECTCOLOR);')  terrified:
      |  ATK is reduced by 50%
    li
      span(style='color:var(--STATUSEFFECTCOLOR);')  obscured:
      |  location is not visible to the opponent
  p
    | status effects typically persist for 4 turns; repeated applications stack by duration.
  p
    span(style='color: var(--GENERALHIGHLIGHT);') true
    |  damage is applied directly and is not affected by hero stats or statuses.
  br
  p
    | heroes are defeated when their HP reaches zero. a hero&apos;s passive becomes inactive once they are defeated.
#creatingAnAccount.helpSlide
  h3 creating an account 
    span(style='font-size:12px;font-weight:normal;color:var(--BACKTOTOP);' onclick="scrollToThisDiv('playGameForward')") [back to top]
  p
    | if you have an 
    span(style='color: var(--GENERALHIGHLIGHT);') invitation code
    | , you can create an account.
  br
  p
    | your 
    span(style='color: var(--GENERALHIGHLIGHT);') username
    |  reserves a nickname for your usage and assigns you a new invitation code that can be used up to five times.
  p
    i please do not create multiple accounts to reserve nicknames or gain more invitation codes: your account (and all resulting accounts) will be removed.
  br
  p
    | accounts track your wins and losses across games and calculate your 
    span(style='color: var(--GENERALHIGHLIGHT);') player score, 
    | which is used to determine your 
    span(style='color: var(--GENERALHIGHLIGHT);') class 
    | and 
    span(style='color: var(--GENERALHIGHLIGHT);') ranking 
    | amongst all players.
  br
  p
    | your 
    span(style='color: var(--GENERALHIGHLIGHT);') class 
    |  is based on your score: 
    span(style='color: var(--IRON);') iron
    | , 
    span(style='color: var(--BRONZE);') bronze
    |  (&gt;15.00), 
    span(style='color: var(--SILVER);') silver
    |  (&gt;20.00), 
    span(style='color: var(--GOLD);') gold
    |  (&gt;30.00), or 
    span(style='color: var(--GRANDMASTER);') grandmaster
    |  (&gt;40.00).
  p
    | if a player is logged in, their name in the lobby will be colored according to their current class. 
  p
    | guest players are shown with 
    span(style='color: var(--NOTIER);') green 
    | names in the lobby. 
  p
    | automated bots are shown with 
    span(style='color: var(--BOTCOLOR') pink 
    | names in the lobby.
  p
    i tip: you can hover over a name in the lobby to have the score and class shown as text.
#scoring.helpSlide
  h3 game scoring 
    span(style='font-size:12px;font-weight:normal;color:var(--BACKTOTOP);' onclick="scrollToThisDiv('playGameForward')") [back to top]
  p
    | when you create an account, your player score is initialized to be 
    span(style='color: var(--GENERALHIGHLIGHT);') 10.00.
  p
    | your player score is updated when you play games while you are logged in.
  br
  p
    | winning a game against a logged-in player grants you 
    span(style='color: var(--GENERALHIGHLIGHT);') 1.00 
    | plus 
    span(style='color: var(--GENERALHIGHLIGHT);') 10% 
    | of your opponent&apos;s score. 
    | at most 
    span(style='color: var(--GENERALHIGHLIGHT);') 5.00 
    | points can be gained per win.
  p
    | losing a game removes 
    span(style='color: var(--GENERALHIGHLIGHT);') 10% 
    | of your own score.
  p
    | surrendering 
    span(style='color:var(--KEYCODE);') (esc) 
    | a game after pick phase completes counts as your opponent's win and your loss.
  br
  p
    | truces (and ties, where both players are simultaneously defeated) affect players' scores, but not players' win/loss counts.
  p
    | if both players tie or agree on a truce 
    span(style='color:var(--KEYCODE);') (t)
    | , both players will receive 
    span(style='color: var(--GENERALHIGHLIGHT);') 0.50 
    | points, and the game will end early.
  br
  p
    span(style='color:var(--GENERALHIGHLIGHT);') disconnecting 
    | after a match starts (e.g. wi-fi disconnecting, closing the window, or refreshing the page) gives your opponent the choice to claim victory or to wait for you to return.
  p
    | if both players disconnect, the match is won by the second player to disconnect, or by neither player if that cannot be determined.
  p
    | after a mutual disconnection, both players will be returned to the lobby page.
#botGames.helpSlide
  h3 bot games 
    span(style='font-size:12px;font-weight:normal;color:var(--BACKTOTOP);' onclick="scrollToThisDiv('playGameForward')") [back to top]
  p
    | every lobby has an automated 
    span(style='color: var(--GENERALHIGHLIGHT);') bot 
    | available to practice against. 
  p
    | note that this feature is currently under development: hero passives in particular will not function correctly in bot games.
  br
  p
    | if you're logged in and have less than 15.00 points, winning a game against a bot grants you 
    span(style='color: var(--GENERALHIGHLIGHT);') 1.00 
    | point, tying against a bot grants you 
    span(style='color: var(--GENERALHIGHLIGHT);') 0.25 
    | points, and losing against a bot grants you no points.
  br
  p
    | if you have accumulated over 15.00 points, bot games will not affect your score at all.
#joiningAGroup.helpSlide
  h3 joining a group 
    span(style='font-size:12px;font-weight:normal;color:var(--BACKTOTOP);' onclick="scrollToThisDiv('playGameForward')") [back to top]
  p
    | after logging in, your account login box will display a space where you can type in the name of your desired 
    span(style='color: var(--GENERALHIGHLIGHT);') group.
  p
    | once you've joined a group, you'll see a list of all of your group members, as well as their scores and win counts.
  p
    | the sum of the group members' scores is the 
    span(style='color: var(--GENERALHIGHLIGHT);') group score, 
    | which is used to determine group rankings.
